On the bridge LORD ELDER sat in the lonely command chair staring at
the viewscreen, his optics dark and thoughtful.

The doors opened and in walked LEGACY, the Maximal&#39;s temporal
guardian, and all around engieneer, scientist and historian. With a
cool detatchment his single optic  took in the entire bridge in one
glance.

BUMP, the Maximal Physicist followed in closely behind, he looking
more uncomfortable on the bridge.

&quot;You called for us.&quot; LEGACY said with his usual abruptness.

LORD ELDER turned to rgard them both. &quot;The crew has left to move to
Crynosis as we discussed.&quot;

LEGACY nodded, although from BUMP&#39;s expression he had no idea of what
ELDER was talking about.

&quot;So now only ourselves and Talon and Elita remain here at the Ark.&quot;
LEGACY stated matter of factly.

There was a grim smile from LORD ELDER as he turned back to the
viewscreen. &quot;Yes. Talon is watching over Elita, but there is nothing
that they can do but wait like the rest of us.&quot;

&quot;Silverbolt is still in the infirmery.&quot; BUMP said, &quot;But I don&#39;t know
when he will awaken.&quot;

ELDER turned to look at the both of them again, &quot;That is what I wanted
to let you know. The group of us. We are all that&#39;s left to mind the
store.&quot;

LEGACY looked at him with a curious expression.

LORDE ELDER chuckled, &quot;With all your knowledge you don&#39;t know that
Earth idiom.&quot; He waved a hand at him as he turned back to the
viewscreen as it depicted the shuttle disapearing out of view. &quot;I will
have to explain it to you sometime.&quot;

